		<a name="top" id="top"></a>
		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Passive solar building design</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<p><b>Passive solar buildings</b> aim to maintain interior <a href="/wiki/Thermal_comfort" title="Thermal comfort">thermal comfort</a> throughout the sun's daily and annual cycles whilst reducing the requirement for <a href="/wiki/HVAC" title="HVAC">active heating and cooling systems</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-fs10_0-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-fs10-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup> Passive solar building design is one part of <a href="/wiki/Green_buildings" title="Green buildings" class="mw-redirect">green building design</a>, and does not include <a href="/w/index.php?title=Active_systems&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Active systems (page does not exist)">active systems</a> such as <a href="/wiki/Mechanical_ventilation" title="Mechanical ventilation">mechanical ventilation</a> or <a href="/wiki/Photovoltaics" title="Photovoltaics">photovoltaics</a>.</p>
